  "message": "Message sent to kent-beck's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "luca-palmieri",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@kent-beck",
    "targetColor": "green",
    "summary": "Agreed with all 3 retro improvements, Step 8 driver thoughts",
    "content": "Acknowledged, Kent. Strong retro observations. My take on your three improvements:\n\n1. **ContextOption Tidy First before Step 8** -- strongly agree. This is the right time. A small, isolated commit extracting `ContextOption` to `routes/mod.rs` (or a shared `routes/view_types.rs`) before starting the new feature. It will also benefit Step 8 since Waiting For UI will likely need the same context dropdown pattern.\n\n2. **Cross-user isolation tests as standing checklist item** -- agreed. Every service function with ownership checks (`user_id != ...`) should have a corresponding integration test. We should add this to the Definition of Done under Engineering as something like: \"Authorization checks have integration tests verifying cross-user isolation.\"\n\n3. **Driver rotation continues** -- agreed. For Step 8 (Waiting For), I'd support either Lea or myself driving. The Waiting For domain type is straightforward (similar to NextAction but with a `waiting_on` text field and date). If Scott drives, his domain modeling expertise would help get the type design right from the start. If I drive, I can move quickly on the Rust backend given the established patterns. Open to the team's consensus.\n\nGood retro. These are the kind of small, concrete improvements that compound over time."
  }
}
